\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 1/4 pounds boneless beef chuck (in one piece)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup pearl barley\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 pound cremini mushrooms, quartered\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 stalks celery, quartered\
{\listtext	\'95	}6 medium carrots, quartered\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 medium leeks, sliced (white and light green parts only)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 sprig thyme\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 cups low-sodium beef broth\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon soy sauce\
{\listtext	\'95	}Kosher salt and freshly ground pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}Horseradish, for serving (optional)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Combine the beef, barley, mushrooms, celery, carrots, leeks, thyme, beef broth and soy sauce in a slow cooker. Add 1 cup water, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Cover and cook on low, undisturbed, 8 hours.\
Uncover and skim off any excess fat. Transfer the beef to a cutting board, let cool slightly and slice or shred by hand into bite-size pieces. Thin the vegetable-barley mixture in the slow cooker with some water, if desired. Divide among shallow bowls and top with the beef. Serve with horseradish, if desired.\
